observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Program Coordinator of the TUPAD Program:
retain copies of all the integral parts of the Memorandum of Agreement with DOLE and strictly comply with all its provisions;
submit  to the Audit Team the lacking necessary documents listed in paragraph 10.4, to validate the disbursements totaling ₱487,500.00.

We recommended and management agreed that the Local Chief Executive should:
Install internal control system over collections and deposits in order to properly safeguard its assets and records and to promote operational efficiency. Regular evaluation of controls should be undertaken to identify procedural problems resulting in deficiencies and inaccurate reports;
Direct the Accountant to adjust the overstated collections in 2020 amounting to ₱161,548.15 and understated government equity amounting to ₱16,278.00;
Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to separate the collections for General Fund, Trust Fund and Special Education Fund to avoid certain errors such as deposit of collections from TF to SEF account. Monitor and follow up the remittances of the RCC daily to avoid overdue collections in the hands of the RCCs;
Direct the Municipal Treasurer to install strict monitoring in the issuance of Accountable Forms to safeguard against possible loss and misuse;
Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to ensure that collections are deposited intact to avoid discrepancies in the cash balances; and
Instruct the Accountant and Treasurer to reconcile monthly the balance of Cash in Local Treasury to avoid errors in recording of collections and deposits.
